FBIS4-9535 "dreeu082_p_94012" FBIS-EEU-94-082 Daily Report 27 Apr 1994 POLAND Further Reportage on Nationwide Strike Further Reportage on Nationwide Strike Communique Labeled `Horrid Document' LD2704210994 Warsaw Third Program Radio Network in Polish 2000 GMT 27 Apr 94 LD2704210994 Warsaw Third Program Radio Network Polish BFN [Excerpt] This is a horrid document, written in the language of totalitarian power on the subject of strikes in the '80's, we were told by Solidarity Chairman Marian Krzaklewski, who was commenting on the text of the communique from the Government Press Office regarding the strike situation in Poland. In a communique published today, the government stressed that strikes in brown coal mines were a threat to the power supply of Poland and that any spreading of the strike action could wreck any chance of economic development. [passage omitted]
